The ring of dueling is a teleportation ring that may be made by casting Lvl-2 Enchant on an emerald ring, granting 37 Magic experience. A full ring of dueling will provide 8 teleports before it crumbles away into nothing. Due to the low cost of the ring, many players use it to bank quickly at the Castle Wars chest. Furthermore, the Ferox Enclave teleport allows a player to use the Pool of Refreshment whilst gaining full health, prayer and run energy, although the Ferox Enclave teleport places the player slightly farther away from a bank chest.

When a ring of dueling has one charge remaining, it is recommended not to use the last charge, but instead to save it and cast High Level Alchemy on it later, as it has the same value as a fully charged ring.

Each charge costs 100.63 coins if all 8 charges are used, 30.57 if using High Level Alchemy (as mentioned above), or 67 if using Low Level Alchemy. Alternatively, Explorer's ring can be used 30 times per day for a cost of 42.14. This is viable if fewer than 210 charges are used on average each day, though it gives no Magic experience.
